<DOC><DOCNO> AP900726-0055 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-26-90 0739EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-France-Attack     07-26 0206</FIRST><SECOND>PM-France-Attack,0211</SECOND><HEAD>Jewish Youths Attacked With Baseball Bats</HEAD><DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Several men armed with baseball bats attacked agroup of Jewish youths before dawn today in the chic Opera districtof the capital, police sources and a French news agency reported.   A reporter for Agence France-Presse said he was among severalwitnesses to the attack, carried out by unidentified young men atabout 1 a.m.   According to the agency, the attackers approached a parked carcontaining an unspecified number of young Jewish men, recognizableby their yarmulkes.   The gang pulled the Jewish youths out of the car and clubbedthem, injuring at least two seriously enough to require emergencytreatment and hospitalization later, AFP reported. The attackersfled, menacing bystanders with their bats.   Police sources confirmed the AFP account and said two men werelater taken into custody and were being held pending identificationby witnesses to the attack. The specific motive for the attack wasnot known.   A wave of anti-Semitic vandalism followed the desecration in Mayof a Jewish cemetery in Carpentras, where a corpse was dug up. Theincidents shocking the country and drew loud denunciations frommost political leaders about a perceived rise of anti-Semitic andanti-immigrant feeling in France.</TEXT></DOC>